Package: scx-quicksched
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Latency-optimised sched_ext CPU scheduler
 Quicksched is a BPF-based CPU scheduler built on sched_ext that keeps
 interactive tasks snappy by separating them from batch and background work.
 .
 Tasks are classified into two tiers: interactive (short 5 ms slices, runs at
 full CPU frequency) and batch (20 ms slices, throttled CPU frequency).
 Classification uses nice value and an EWMA sleep-ratio so I/O-bound tasks are
 promoted automatically without manual tuning. Memory pressure (PSI) is also
 tracked and fed back to the scheduler via BPF maps for live throttling.
 .
 Requires Linux kernel >= 6.12 with CONFIG_SCHED_CLASS_EXT=y.
